#Requires AutoHotkey v2.0

; Copy into src/Lib/Modules/ under a real name (e.g. AutoRepairModule.ahk),
; delete this comment block, and fill in the sections below. This is the
; ONLY place your macro's logic should live — both the standalone wrapper
; (see templates/NewMacro.ahk.example) and src/DDToolkit.ahk #Include this
; same file and call the same Init(), so there is exactly one copy of the
; behavior to keep correct.
;
; 1. Add any tunables to config/settings.ini under a new [NewMacro]
;    section, including "Enabled=true" — every module must support being
;    turned off from DDToolkit's settings window.
; 2. State lives in `static` class properties, not bare globals — several
;    modules run in the same process inside DDToolkit.ahk, and plain
;    globals with common names (like "running" or "intervalMs") would
;    clobber each other.
; 3. Static properties must be declared with `static Name := default` in
;    the class body — assigning `this.Name := value` from inside a method
;    to a name that was never declared isn't guaranteed to create a real
;    static property in AHK v2.
; 4. Keep every hotkey scoped to the game: `HotIfWinActive(DD.GameCriterion())`
;    / `Hotkey(...)` / `HotIfWinActive()` (reset) — unless you have a
;    specific documented reason for it to work globally (see
;    AutoClickerModule, which is deliberately general-purpose behind its
;    own ScopeToGame setting).
; 5. Give the user audible/visual feedback on every state change —
;    DD.Beep(bool) / DD.Notify(title, text) — never a silent toggle.
; 6. Implement StatusText() — one short line, shown in DDToolkit's tray
;    tooltip and usable by the standalone wrapper's startup notification.
class NewMacroModule {
    static Enabled := false
    static ToggleKey := "F4"
    static Running := false

    static Init() {
        this.Enabled := DD.ReadBool("NewMacro", "Enabled", true)
        if !this.Enabled
            return

        this.ToggleKey := DD.Read("NewMacro", "ToggleKey", "F4")
        this.Running := false

        HotIfWinActive(DD.GameCriterion())
        Hotkey(this.ToggleKey, ObjBindMethod(this, "Toggle"))
        HotIfWinActive()
    }

    static Toggle(*) {
        this.Running := !this.Running
        DD.Beep(this.Running)
        ; Your Send/Click/whatever goes here, or wire up a SetTimer like
        ; AutoAbilityModule does for a repeating action.
    }

    static StatusText() {
        if !this.Enabled
            return "NewMacro : desactive"
        return "NewMacro : " (this.Running ? "arme" : "au repos") " (" this.ToggleKey ")"
    }
}
